metadata.name: Flowingcles #47
metadata.description:
"Flowingcles" is a generative art piece that showcases a mesmerizing collection of  circles and abstract shapes. This unique collection invites art enthusiasts to embark on an inspiring visual journey.

Some pieces feature abstract shapes accompanied by a noise effect, reflecting restlessness and energy, while others present a more serene atmosphere with minimalized noise effects. These two approaches offer collectors the freedom to choose the one that resonates with them the most.

The "Flowingcles" collection consists of a total of 128 original pieces. Each artwork has been generated with a unique combination, ensuring individuality and distinctiveness. By incorporating these pieces into their collections, art enthusiasts can adorn their homes, offices, or galleries with a sense of unparalleled art experience and authenticity.

"Flowingcles" stands as a prominent example of modern art, showcasing dynamism, aesthetics, and originality. This collection pushes the boundaries of art and takes viewers on a captivating visual journey. Therefore, me invite art lovers to explore the "Flowingcles" collection and become a part of this visual spectacle:)

- S: Save a png file with the current resolution (2400*3400)

metadata.name: Threads: An algorithm study #14
metadata.description:
This series of my algorithmic studies is an exploration of animation algorithms to create an abstract artwork using connected lines.
This artwork is created with only lines and shadows to create a sense of connected threads with a special algorithm. Multiple color palettes have been used. It takes a short time for animation to complete.

Made with p5js.

metadata.name: Poem Of Atoms #91
metadata.description:
There is a force in the universe that binds everything together
It's a electronic web that connects everything in a delicate balance. 
Some call it fate. But few know the truth.
They are the lifeblood of our society, and they are what keep us moving forward. We are constantly surrounded by them, and they are always changing. It's not a force, it's an orbit. And the dots are the energy sources.

Made with P5js

metadata.name: Apertum #19
metadata.description:
Welcome to 'Apertum', a project that combines simple geometric elements with the unpredictability of randomness. It starts with triangles and lines and results in a diverse array of formations.

In 'Apertum', you will find a series of transformations and reshuffles, as well as a vibrant mix of textures and patterns. These interactions give rise to intricate compositions that I hope you'll enjoy discovering.

'Apertum' is both a thank you to those who have supported my work so far and an invitation to those new to my creations. I invite you to step into the world of 'Apertum', to discover its interplay of shapes, colors, and textures.

Press [s] to save a .png file of the artwork. Made with p5.js

Rob Scalera | 2023

metadata.name: lsland Of Mountains #16
metadata.description:
The mountains account for 70% of Taiwan's land area and are so dense that they are known as the "Island of Mountains".
moreover,only 1% of the world's forests can be called fog forests, and Taiwan is among them.
due to regional differences in climate, geological history and phytogeography,the mountain forests have a high diversity of plants and animals,which attracts many climbers to make the trip.

山岳總面積佔據了臺灣土地面積70%，高山密度之高，足以譽為「群山之島」。
不僅如此，全世界只有1%的森林可以稱之為霧林，台灣也在其中。
由於區域氣候的差異，以及地質史及植物地理學的因素,
山地霧林擁有極高的植物及動物的多樣性，更是吸引無數爬山愛好者前來觀光。

metadata.name: MAGNETIK #14
metadata.description:
The output of MAGNETIK reminds me of what tornadoes do to our cities and buildings, yet I imagine the pieces that are about to break off and fly away to be made of metal foil and they do so because of a magnetic force that is pulling them away from where they belong…  This one is also a charity run :  
- 20% of the primary sales will go directly to the Processing Foundation, 

- Remaining 80% will be donated to a group of individuals that raise money to buy computers for less fortunate architecture students in a university in the eastern part of Turkey. Please read the next paragraph for a detailed explanation

- I will decide what to do with the secondary sales later if there will be any.

About the majority (80%) of the donation : I decided that the donations should be done in a double-blind way, the donator does not know who they are donating to, and the receivers of the donation will not know from whom the donation is coming from, hence I will transfer the funds these individuals mentioned to act as a middle-step. I feel like this is a hard thing to provide a solid proof for, so I recommend if you have doubts and/or straight away do not trust me or this process, do not mint. I will only be able to provide proof of transfer of funds to a third-party. I trust the people I am sending the funds to, we have done this before (not to brag or anything) and I know that we are affecting younger people’s life in a good way. Also, I believe that the funds raised from this project alone will not be enough to buy one decent config. computer by itself, if it were so, I would have done it differently.  About MAGNETIK :  
MAGNETIK plays on the idea of distorting and breaking grids by employing an illusion of fake 3D and tries to make the resulting composition look good with rhythm and color harmony.
 
- 21 palettes,
- 2 background modes : lights on / lights off,
- 3 grid types,
- plus some surprise features…

I encourage you to try and see the variations before minting :)  2 of the grid types are based on https://gorillasun.de/blog/an-algorithm-for-irregular-grids by Ahmad Moussa ( https://twitter.com/gorillasu ) and used with his knowledge and kind permission.

gradient formulas are based on https://twitter.com/takawo/status/1505876107492720651?s=20&t=S9aU_oNYyjBieBcEmvUV-g
by Takawo Shunsuke ( https://twitter.com/takawo ) and used with his knowledge and kind permission.

Thank you all in advance and have a good day!

DISCLAIMER : I am not a good coder, I have tried to fix my past mistakes from my earlier projects to make some room for new mistakes :) I am hoping that there isn’t any huge bugs or anything left so you can enjoy your mint! Please hit me up if you have any concerns after minting and we can discuss a solution.

metadata.name: Obscured by Clouds #20
metadata.description:
This artwork is an attempt to create a painterly texture and to keep the focus on just the paint rather than any object it fills. It's coded in p5.js and uses overlapping translucent shapes to create the texture.

Best viewed on a screen bigger than a mobile phone, while listening to this track called 'Obscured by Clouds' by Pink Floyd: https://open.spotify.com/track/3c8LKbUsjW9lMYQzVScXQT
Press 's' to save the image

Credits:
 - Technique is inspired by this essay by Tyler Hobbs: https://tylerxhobbs.com/essays/2020/how-to-hack-a-painting
 - The name of the artwork is a tribute to my favourite band
